<br>
Then came melee balancing and rangers turned into an easier class to play.. we weren't as group dependant.. groups were wanting us a bit more than before.. got panic animal to do some soloing, etc.. <br>
<br>
Anyways.. i beg to differ.. i kinda think Clerics (or you're local healer) are the &quot;hardest&quot; to play.. at the least they require the most attention imo.. you can't really go AFK as the only healer in an exp group and expect to come back to more exp than you went AFK with.. but if another class did you still could.<br>
<br>
Raid envirorments being so dependant upon clerics makes them tough to play especialy if you are tight on clerics (for example you dont have a lot of room for error).. if you miss a spot in you're CH order and no one covers you or something, the MT will die and quite possibly the rest of the raid.<br>
<br>
Bards dont seem that hard to me.. i guess a GOOD bard is hard to play, but typically, a bard can AFK with a song on or something.. doesn't make them a good bard but they are still doable and helpful =p <p><center>
